The paper deals with entity type classification, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, the focus of the paper is on personal data entities, which are sensitive and require fine-grained classification for compliance with regulations such as GDPR and HIPAA. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper proposes a neural model for classification, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
